<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="16" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1399,1419,1557]" pageId="16" pageNumber="16">
The Guineo-Congolian genus 
<taxonomicName box="[549,714,1419,1445]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[549,714,1419,1445]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="16">Smeringopina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is highly diverse in Central Africa but only eight species are known from West Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Huber B. A. &amp; Kwapong P." box="[531,772,1456,1482]" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="16" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 44" part="59" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2013.59" refString="Huber B. A. &amp; Kwapong P. 2013. West African pholcid spiders: an overview, with descriptions of five new species (Araneae, Pholcidae). European Journal of Taxonomy 59: 1 - 44. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2013.59" title="West African pholcid spiders: an overview, with descriptions of five new species (Araneae, Pholcidae)" type="journal article" year="2013">
Huber 2013; 
<figureCitation box="[686,772,1456,1482]" captionStart="Figs 31 - 32" captionStartId="15.[189,241,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,536,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[189,1399,536,1925]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 31 - 32. Known distributions of the genera Physocyclus Simon, 1893 and Smeringopina Kraus, 1957 in West Africa." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1406604/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="16">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
). Most species belong to one of the two endemic West African species groups, the 
<taxonomicName box="[524,648,1494,1519]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guineensis">
<emphasis box="[524,648,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="16">guineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and the 
<taxonomicName box="[832,915,1493,1519]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ankasa">
<emphasis box="[832,915,1493,1519]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="16">ankasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Huber B. A. &amp; Kwapong P." box="[1011,1158,1493,1519]" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="16" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 44" part="59" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2013.59" refString="Huber B. A. &amp; Kwapong P. 2013. West African pholcid spiders: an overview, with descriptions of five new species (Araneae, Pholcidae). European Journal of Taxonomy 59: 1 - 44. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2013.59" title="West African pholcid spiders: an overview, with descriptions of five new species (Araneae, Pholcidae)" type="journal article" year="2013">Huber 2013</bibRefCitation>
); only 
<taxonomicName authority="Kraus, 1957" authorityName="Kraus" authorityYear="1957" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Smeringopina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beninensis">
<emphasis box="[1243,1399,1493,1519]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="16">S. beninensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kraus O." box="[189,333,1530,1557]" journalOrPublisher="Senckenbergiana biologica" pageId="16" pageNumber="16" pagination="217 - 243" part="38" refString="Kraus O. 1957. Araneenstudien 1. Pholcidae (Smeringopodinae, Ninetinae). Senckenbergiana biologica 38 (3 / 4): 217 - 243." title="Araneenstudien 1. Pholcidae (Smeringopodinae, Ninetinae)" type="journal article" year="1957">Kraus, 1957</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a notable outlier of a group otherwise restricted to Central Africa.
</paragraph>
